    Profiling forecaster fit¶

    In order to exclude the training process of the regressor, a summy regressor class is created.m

    In [7]:
    Copied! 
    class DummyRegressor(LinearRegression):
    '''
    '''
    
    def fit(self, X, y):
        pass

    def predict(self, y):
        predictions = np.ones(shape = len(y))
        return predictions
    class DummyRegressor(LinearRegression): ''' ''' def fit(self, X, y): pass def predict(self, y): predictions = np.ones(shape = len(y)) return predictions

    Profiling create train matrix¶

    In [8]:
    Copied! 
    series_length = np.geomspace(1000, 1000000, num=3, dtype=int)
n_lags = [5, 10, 50, 100, 200]
results = {}

for lags in n_lags:
    execution_time = []
    forecaster = ForecasterAutoreg(
                    regressor = DummyRegressor(),
                    lags      = lags
                 )

    for n in series_length:
        y = pd.Series(data = np.random.normal(size=n))
        tic = time.perf_counter()
        _ = forecaster.create_train_X_y(y=y)
        toc = time.perf_counter()
        execution_time.append(toc-tic)

    results[lags] = execution_time

results = pd.DataFrame(
            data =  results,
            index = series_length
        )

results
    series_length = np.geomspace(1000, 1000000, num=3, dtype=int) n_lags = [5, 10, 50, 100, 200] results = {} for lags in n_lags: execution_time = [] forecaster = ForecasterAutoreg( regressor = DummyRegressor(), lags = lags ) for n in series_length: y = pd.Series(data = np.random.normal(size=n)) tic = time.perf_counter() _ = forecaster.create_train_X_y(y=y) toc = time.perf_counter() execution_time.append(toc-tic) results[lags] = execution_time results = pd.DataFrame( data = results, index = series_length ) results
